00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:05,950
你说我们的做法并不违法
You said what we're doing wasn't illegal.

334
00:22:05,950 --> 00:22:08,180
不  我说是灰色地带  不受监管
No, I said it was gray, that it's unregulated.

335
00:22:08,180 --> 00:22:10,340
我们的数据是私有的
Our data is proprietary.

336
00:22:10,340 --> 00:22:12,110
我们如何使用  是我们的特权
How we want to use it, it's our prerogative.

337
00:22:12,110 --> 00:22:15,390
如果他们给分享那些数据的利益估价
If they put a value on the benefits of sharing all that data,

338
00:22:15,390 --> 00:22:18,670
肯定要超过所有竞选经费上限
the figure would break all campaign finance caps there are.

339
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,410
这事怎么泄露出去的
How the fuck did this get out?

340
00:22:21,510 --> 00:22:23,810
先生  那名记者不是我们记者团的
Sir? That reporter's not in our press pool.

341
00:22:23,810 --> 00:22:26,450
-我们没给他认证  -那么他为谁工作
- We didn't credential him ourselves. - So, who does he work for?

342
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:28,410
我们还在努力查证
We're still trying to track that down.

343
00:22:29,490 --> 00:22:30,540
把你的手机给我
Give me your phone.

344
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:36,030
我这就给您接通  先生
I'll connect you now, sir.

345
00:22:36,030 --> 00:22:37,490
您已经在跟总统通话了
You are now on with the president.

346
00:22:37,490 --> 00:22:39,010
我得说  我很失望
I must say, I'm disappointed.

347
00:22:39,010 --> 00:22:42,010
我还希望我们第一次见面会是当面见呢
I was hoping the first time we met would be in person.

348
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:44,960
-我们见过的  -是啊  对了
- We've met before. - Oh, yes, that's right.

349
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:46,920
你知道我打来是为什么事  总统先生
You know why I'm calling, Mr. President.

350
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:49,820
不知道  但我的确读到了一些有趣的文章
No, but I have been reading some curious articles.

351
00:22:49,820 --> 00:22:53,000
你觉得这些报道要多久就会成为主流
How long before you think it becomes mainstream?

352
00:22:53,050 --> 00:22:54,840
你安排了那名记者
You planted that reporter.

353
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:58,570
我可没有  你是谬赞我了
I did not. You're giving me far more credit than I deserve.

354
00:22:58,570 --> 00:23:00,970
如果你把司法部扯进来
If you bring the Justice Department into this,

355
00:23:01,040 --> 00:23:03,440
我会在滥用职权上对你穷追猛打
I'll come down hard on you for abuse of power,

356
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:05,920
那对你的伤害不会少于对我的伤害
and that'll hurt you just as much as it hurts me.

357
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:07,840
我不用  他们跟其他人一样
I won't have to. They read the newspapers,

358
00:23:07,850 --> 00:23:09,610
也会看报纸
just like everyone else.

359
00:23:10,050 --> 00:23:11,660
那你最好拉住他们
Well, then you better hold them back.

360
00:23:11,660 --> 00:23:13,140
我提醒你一下  州长
Let me remind you, Governor,

361
00:23:13,140 --> 00:23:15,410
以防你哪天真当上了总统
in case you do become president one day,

362
00:23:15,410 --> 00:23:17,750
司法部是自主的
the Justice Department is autonomous.

363
00:23:17,750 --> 00:23:19,880
我干涉可是违法的
If I were to intervene, it would be illegal.

364
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:21,880
就像你抢了联邦应急管理署那次吗
Just like when you raided FEMA?

365
00:23:22,040 --> 00:23:24,520
瞧  全国都想相信你腐败
See, the country wants to believe that you're corrupt,

366
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:26,890
我会画道线把你和...
and I'll draw a very clear line between you--

367
00:23:26,890 --> 00:23:29,300
你做吧  这事闹得越大越好
Go ahead. The more volume on this, the better.

368
00:23:29,300 --> 00:23:33,040
你提出指控  我就让媒体以事实回应
You hurl accusations, I'll let the press hurl facts.

369
00:23:33,940 --> 00:23:36,180
但你究竟想做什么呢
But what did you really hope to achieve?

370
00:23:36,390 --> 00:23:38,180
我觉得你浪费了时间
I think you've wasted your time.

371
00:23:38,180 --> 00:23:41,040
你真有筹码的时候该打给我的
You should have called me when you had some actual leverage.

372
00:23:41,040 --> 00:23:43,900
但我得说  听到你如此激动真是令人喜出望外
But I must say, it is a treat to hear you so worked up.

373
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:45,400
多谢了
I do thank you for that.

374
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:48,750
"华盛顿  杰斐逊  林肯
"Washington, Jefferson, Lincoln.

375
00:23:48,750 --> 00:23:52,080
高个子能当好总统"  我们初遇时你对我说的
Tall men make good presidents." You said that when we first met.

376
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:54,590
是的  我记得
Yes, I remember what I said.

377
00:23:55,510 --> 00:23:56,980
你当时怕了
You were intimidated.

378
00:23:57,660 --> 00:24:00,930
我并不低估你  州长  但怕你
I don't underestimate you, Governor. But intimidated?

379
00:24:00,930 --> 00:24:04,880
光是海拔和自大可不足以让我害怕
Takes a lot more than height and arrogance to intimidate me.

380
00:24:05,220 --> 00:24:07,800
你赶快回你的律师身边吧
You better get back to all your lawyers.

381
00:24:12,740 --> 00:24:14,490
罗马将军苏拉
When the Roman general Sulla,

382
00:24:14,490 --> 00:24:16,590
大约我现在这年纪时
who was about the same age I am now,

383
00:24:16,590 --> 00:24:19,500
向罗马进军  清除城内叛军
marched on Rome to purge the city of usurpers,

384
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:21,100
当时血流成河
it was a bloodbath.

385
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:24,390
他最大的对手是一个叫马吕斯的年轻人
His greatest rival was a young man named Marius,

386
00:24:24,390 --> 00:24:26,290
才26岁
who was just 26 years old.

387
00:24:26,290 --> 00:24:27,930
苏拉杀了他之后
And after Sulla had him killed,

388
00:24:27,930 --> 00:24:30,030
他在广场上举起了他的头
he held up his head in the forum

389
00:24:30,030 --> 00:24:32,480
盯着男孩无光的眼睛说
and looked into the boy's dead eyes

390
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:35,680
"首先  你得学会摇桨
and said, "First, you must learn to pull an oar.

391
00:24:35,680 --> 00:24:38,540
然后才能掌舵"
Only then can you take the helm."

392
00:24:43,780 --> 00:24:46,340
高压110  低压80  不赖嘛
110 over 80. Not bad.

393
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:49,120
威尔
Will.

394
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,140
我打给了总统
I called the president.

395
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:02,410
是个错误
It was a mistake.

396
00:25:03,410 --> 00:25:04,300
好吧
Okay.

397
00:25:06,870 --> 00:25:12,280
听着  我们回楼上去
Look, um... why don't we go back upstairs

398
00:25:12,630 --> 00:25:14,230
筹点钱吧
and collect some money?

399
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:17,640
好吗  大家都想见你
Okay? Everyone wants to see you.

400
00:25:26,820 --> 00:25:28,830
-走吧  -你会想出对策的
- Let's go. - You'll figure it out.

401
00:25:40,530 --> 00:25:44,330
康威打来了  想跟我做交易
Conway called. He wanted to make a deal.

402
00:25:45,150 --> 00:25:46,630
肯定很有意思吧
I'm sure that was enjoyable.

403
00:25:46,630 --> 00:25:47,810
等司法部插手了
It will be even more so

404
00:25:47,810 --> 00:25:50,260
会更有意思的
once the Justice Department gets involved.

405
00:25:53,390 --> 00:25:54,650
那是...
Is that the, uh...

406
00:25:55,500 --> 00:25:57,790
同款  不是同一个
Same model. Not the actual one.

407
00:26:04,280 --> 00:26:05,880
-特勤局居然允许...  -那个
- Surprised the Secret Service let - Well,

408
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:08,150
他们拔了撞针
they removed the firing pin.

409
00:26:08,940 --> 00:26:10,840
比我想的要轻
It's lighter than I imagined.

410
00:26:11,830 --> 00:26:15,460
这么小的东西居然能造成那么大的伤害
It's amazing something this small could do that much damage.

411
00:26:17,900 --> 00:26:19,260
我本想明天带上的
I was gonna bring it tomorrow,

412
00:26:19,260 --> 00:26:21,720
但或许太过戏剧化了
but I think it might be too theatrical.

413
00:26:32,120 --> 00:26:35,090
要我帮你练习吗
You want me to help you practice?

414
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:38,380
好
All right.

415
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:44,070
早上好  安德伍德夫人
Good morning, Mrs. Underwood.

416
00:26:44,730 --> 00:26:46,260
早上好  梅尔曼女士
Good morning, Ms. Melman.

417
00:26:46,270 --> 00:26:48,920
-不  她叫什么  -茱莉亚
- No, what's her first name? - Julia.

418
00:26:48,930 --> 00:26:51,580
-叫这个  -我们不认识
- Use that. - We've never met before.

419
00:26:51,620 --> 00:26:53,990
让她知道第一夫人是谁
Remind her who the First Lady is.

420
00:26:57,800 --> 00:26:59,320
早上好  茱莉亚
Good morning, Julia.

421
00:27:00,050 --> 00:27:01,870
早上好  安德伍德夫人
Good morning, Mrs. Underwood.

422
00:27:02,140 --> 00:27:03,330
请坐吧
Please, have a seat.

423
00:27:07,490 --> 00:27:09,360
我们想有包容性
We want to be inclusive.

424
00:27:09,660 --> 00:27:13,450
我们希望全国步枪协会与我们合作让法案通过
We'd like the NRA to work with us on getting this bill passed.

425
00:27:13,450 --> 00:27:16,510
我们在两党都广受支持
We have major support on both sides of the aisle.

426
00:27:16,520 --> 00:27:18,920
那是现在  但今后未必
Well, you do for now, but not for long.

427
00:27:18,920 --> 00:27:21,940
即便是20个孩子死于校园枪击
You can have 20 kids massacred in a school shooting.

428
00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:24,830
公众会愤怒呼吁枪支改革
There's always the usual public outcry, demands for gun reform.

429
00:27:24,830 --> 00:27:27,450
但几个月后  人们就会忘记
But a few months go by and people forget.

430
00:27:27,450 --> 00:27:29,290
这份法案会迅速通过国会
Well, this will move through Congress quickly.

431
00:27:29,290 --> 00:27:31,950
我们在两党都广受支持
We've got major support on both sides of the aisle.

432
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,690
那也不足以打破阻挠议事
Not enough to break a filibuster.

433
00:27:33,690 --> 00:27:35,690
我们会把此事拖到大选
We'll drag this out till the election.

434
00:27:35,690 --> 00:27:37,740
我们会阻挠参议院其他所有的法案
We'll tie up every other bill in the Senate.

435
00:27:37,740 --> 00:27:39,290
我跟很多参议员谈过  他们...
Well, I've spoken to a lot of Senators and they--

436
00:27:39,290 --> 00:27:41,000
不  别跟她纠缠那个
No, don't get bogged down there.

437
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:42,640
把重点直接戳到最高法院
Pivot right to the Supreme Court.

438
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:45,590
你打算连最高法院提名也拖延吗
You plan on holding up the Supreme Court nomination, as well?

439
00:27:45,590 --> 00:27:47,790
除非你打算提名一位全国步枪协会的成员
Unless you're going to nominate an NRA member.

440
00:27:47,790 --> 00:27:50,600
-你知道那不可能  -雅各布斯不好预测
- You know we can't do that. - Jacobs was unpredictable.

441
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:52,310
这次我们不会冒险了
This time we're not taking any chances.

442
00:27:52,310 --> 00:27:54,370
如果你让政府停摆
If you bring the government to a standstill,

443
00:27:54,370 --> 00:27:56,560
我们就把全国步枪协会作为选举重点
we're gonna make this election about the NRA.

444
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:59,530
你拼不过一个亿的广告
You can't match $100 million in ad buys.

445
00:27:59,540 --> 00:28:01,590
去吧  把你的钱都浪费掉吧
Go for it. Flush your money down the drain.

446
00:28:01,590 --> 00:28:04,300
民主党数十年前就输了这场仗了
The Democrats lost that battle decades ago.

447
00:28:04,310 --> 00:28:05,320
你还会再输一次
And you'll lose it again.

448
00:28:05,320 --> 00:28:09,980
总统任党鞭时未提出过一项枪支改革法案
The president never offered up one gun reform bill while he was whip.

449
00:28:09,980 --> 00:28:11,710
因为那当时并非他的首要考虑
Well, because it wasn't a top priority for him--

450
00:28:11,710 --> 00:28:13,710
不不不  更强势点
No, no, no, no, no. Make it, uh, stronger.

451
00:28:13,710 --> 00:28:17,350
比如  "总统挨了颗子弹"  弄成私事
Say, uh, "The president took a bullet!" Make it personal.

452
00:28:17,360 --> 00:28:18,790
我对您丈夫遭枪击感到遗憾
I'm sorry your husband got shot.

453
00:28:19,350 --> 00:28:20,990
但不至于因此妥协
But not enough to roll over.

454
00:28:20,990 --> 00:28:22,680
我们不是叫你妥协
Oh, we're not asking you to.

455
00:28:23,130 --> 00:28:25,820
我们是希望你站在历史正确的一方
We're inviting you to be on the right side of history.

456
00:28:25,860 --> 00:28:28,500
这不错  但你要得拿出致命的招数
Yeah, that's good, but you wanna go in for the kill.

457
00:28:28,500 --> 00:28:31,070
我们要这女人气得夺门而出
We want this woman storming out of that door,

458
00:28:31,070 --> 00:28:32,650
口吐白沫
foaming at the mouth.

459
00:28:32,650 --> 00:28:34,500
好吧  别丢人了  茱莉亚
All right. Don't disgrace yourself, Julia.

460
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:36,180
-想想未来  -不  再强硬点
- Think about the future- - No, tougher.

461
00:28:36,180 --> 00:28:37,790
再狠点  再强硬点
Stronger, tougher!

462
00:28:40,590 --> 00:28:41,850
好吧  那这样如果
All right, what about...

463
00:28:41,990 --> 00:28:44,760
三十年后  当你接受临终护理  奄奄一息时
Thirty years from now when you're dying in hospice care...

464
00:28:45,520 --> 00:28:48,750
你可以回首人生  为你拯救的生命而自豪
you can look back and be proud of all the lives you saved.

465
00:28:48,750 --> 00:28:50,860
也可以被历史遗忘
Or you can be forgotten...

466
00:28:51,780 --> 00:28:54,750
用你冰冷僵硬的双手紧紧抓住过去
clutching onto the past with your cold, dead hands.

467
00:28:55,630 --> 00:28:56,760
我自己出去吧
I'll show myself out.

468
00:28:56,760 --> 00:29:00,560
这就是我说的那份勇气
That's exactly the steel goddamn stomach I was talking about.

469
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:01,740
是皮特·德雷尔吗
Was it Pete Dreyer?

470
00:29:01,750 --> 00:29:04,490
德雷尔议员是我多年的导师
Congressman Dreyer's been a mentor for years.

471
00:29:04,810 --> 00:29:07,730
-他无权告诉你  -他完全有权
- He had no right to tell you. - He had every right.

472
00:29:08,110 --> 00:29:09,620
如果众议院情报委员会的成员
If a member of the House Intelligence Committee

473
00:29:09,630 --> 00:29:13,130
决定对我透露情报  他有这个权利
chooses to share information with me, he's at liberty to do so.

474
00:29:13,130 --> 00:29:15,190
我们的谈话是私下的
Our conversation was in confidence.

475
00:29:15,190 --> 00:29:16,450
这让我很不舒服
I don't feel comfortable with this.

476
00:29:16,450 --> 00:29:18,880
议员跟你一样觉得不满
The Congressman is just as frustrated as you are,

477
00:29:18,880 --> 00:29:21,170
他找到我是因为希望我帮忙
and he spoke to me because he wants to help.

478
00:29:21,590 --> 00:29:23,100
我也想帮忙  将军
And so do I, General.

479
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:26,140
州长  我是名士兵  我不玩政治
Governor, I'm a soldier. I'm not going to play politics.

480
00:29:26,830 --> 00:29:30,780
你对皮特开口的时候就是在玩政治了
You played politics the moment you opened your mouth to Pete.

481
00:29:33,630 --> 00:29:36,580
-你看到我昨天的讲话了吗  -是的
- Did you see my speech yesterday? - Yes, I did.

482
00:29:37,260 --> 00:29:38,760
我都是真心的
I meant every word of it.

483
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:41,600
你我都曾为我们国家而战
Now, you and I have both fought for our country.

484
00:29:41,710 --> 00:29:43,210
安德伍德可没有
Underwood hasn't.

485
00:29:44,130 --> 00:29:46,650
他根本不懂  不能理解
He has no idea. He doesn't understand.

486
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:49,610
所以我得当上总统
And that's why I need to be president,

487
00:29:49,610 --> 00:29:52,520
这样我们才能在需要的时候出击
so we can strike when we need to strike.

488
00:29:52,520 --> 00:29:56,630
听着  我可以帮你  但我需要你的帮助
Look, I can help you, but I need your help to do so.

489
00:29:57,330 --> 00:30:01,430
我从未向媒体透露过机密信息  从没有过
I've never leaked classified information to the press. Not once.

490
00:30:01,970 --> 00:30:04,650
我的同事干过  我没有过
My colleagues have. I haven't.

491
00:30:04,650 --> 00:30:05,960
有个更好的办法
There's a better way.

492
00:30:06,270 --> 00:30:08,110
你起初会觉得不太好
You're not gonna like the sound of this at first,

493
00:30:08,120 --> 00:30:12,170
但只要你听我说完  我们可以施以回击
but if you hear me out, we can fight back on this.

494
00:30:12,290 --> 00:30:13,970
-将军  -总统先生
- General. - Mr. President.

495
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:21,720
收回去吧  我不接受你的辞职
You can take this back. I am not accepting your resignation.

496
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:22,720
请坐
Please, sit.

497
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:26,000
我曾在黎巴嫩作战  先生
I fought in Lebanon, sir.

498
00:30:26,460 --> 00:30:28,040
在索马里
Commanded troops in Somalia,

499
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:30,810
波斯尼亚  两次海湾战争和阿富汗带过兵
in Bosnia, in both Gulf Wars, in Afghanistan.

500
00:30:30,950 --> 00:30:33,920
我不希望我们再在那样的冲突中陷入困境
I just don't wanna see us bogged down in another conflict like those.

501
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:36,820
哈里发国就是下一个基地组织和塔利班
ICO is the next Al Qaeda and Taliban.

